# Authorised release signers for mus.
#
# This file is consumed by `git verify-tag`, `git verify-commit`, and
# `ssh-keygen -Y verify` to confirm that a release artifact was signed by an
# expected identity.
#
# Format (see git-config(1) `gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile` and ssh-keygen(1)
# `ALLOWED SIGNERS`): one entry per line:
#
#   <principal>   [namespaces=...]   <ssh-pubkey>
#
# To verify a checksum file:
#   ssh-keygen -Y verify -f .gitsigners \
#       -I mark.fiers@kuleuven.be \
#       -n file \
#       -s dist/SHA256SUMS.sig < dist/SHA256SUMS
#
# To verify a git tag:
#   git -c gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile=.gitsigners verify-tag v0.1.0
#
# Trust-bootstrapping note: the entry below is committed inside the repo it
# verifies, so a clone alone cannot prove it was not tampered with. Cross-check
# the public key against https://codeberg.org/atrxia.keys before treating
# signatures as authoritative.

mark.fiers@kuleuven.be namespaces="git,file" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHP0TEW6QS203/gQ9ch11yWEnHrOZwsrWtUnxyLsDpEn
